Title: Series: Ars moriendi
Description: Sheet 8: suggestion of humbleness against haughtiness; a man in sickbed, surrounded by three angels, the Trinity, the Virgin and St Antony; the jaws of hell and two demons are depicted in the left lower foreground Engraving with hand-colouring
Producer name: Print made by: Master of the Blumenrahmen
Curator's comments: Part of a series, consisting of eleven sheets (L114-124), copied in reverse after the Master ES (L 175-185). The complete set is extant at the BM.
Bibliographic references: Lehrs 1908-34 / Geschichte und kritische Katalog des deutschen, niederländischen und französischen Kupferstichs im XV Jahrhundert (III.227.121)
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
